  "prompt": "Who are the best 5 left handed fast bowlers in Indian domestic cricket after Zaheer Khan's retirement?",
  "response": "Evaluating the best left-handed fast bowlers in Indian domestic cricket post Zaheer Khan's retirement involves considering their performance, consistency, and impact on the game. While opinions may vary, some notable left-handed fast bowlers in recent years include:\n\n1. **Jaydev Unadkat**: Unadkat has been a standout performer in domestic cricket, consistently leading the wicket charts in tournaments like the Ranji Trophy. His leadership and experience have made him a crucial player for Saurashtra.\n\n2. **Khaleel Ahmed**: A promising young talent, Ahmed has shown considerable potential in the domestic circuit and has also represented India in limited-overs cricket. His pace and ability to swing the ball make him a valuable asset.\n\n3. **Sreenath Aravind**: Although not as prominent as others, Aravind has had success with Karnataka in domestic competitions, contributing significantly with his left-arm pace bowling.\n\n4. **Aniket Choudhary**: Choudhary has been a consistent performer for Rajasthan in domestic cricket. His height and ability to extract bounce make him an effective bowler in various conditions.\n\n5. **T. Natarajan**: Known for his ability to bowl yorkers and his impressive performances in limited-overs cricket, Natarajan has emerged as a promising bowler. His performance in the IPL and subsequent selection for the Indian T20 squad has highlighted his skills.\n\nThese bowlers have made significant contributions to Indian domestic cricket through their skill, dedication, and performance.",
